        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:13PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Crossett, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
North Crossett, Crossett, and West Crossett around 420 PM CDT.
Hamburg and Berlin around 435 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for
southeastern Arkansas...and northeastern Louisiana.</instruction>
